    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-04-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-04-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="522"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d522">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">894.00/4–348: Airgram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Acting Political Adviser in Japan</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sebald</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-04-03">April 3,
                            1948</date>.<lb/>[Received April 8—9:51 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>A–66. For the Department’s information, there follows the text of a press release
                    issued by the Public Information Office, General Headquarters, Far East Command
                    on April 1, 1948: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Brig. Gen. Courtney Whitney, Chief of <gloss target="#t_SCAP1"
                                >SCAP’s</gloss> Government Section, has pointed out that the purge
                            program, while fully consistent <pb facs="0736" n="722" xml:id="pg_722"
                            /> with the purposes of the Japanese Government and people in charting a
                            democratic future, is one of the direct requirements of the Potsdam
                            Declaration. As such, final action taken thereunder is regarded to be of
                            a permanent nature for which the Allied powers will unquestionably hold
                            future Japanese governments fully responsible.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sebald</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
